  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Keil and Delitzsch Biblical Commentary on the Old Testament",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "And they cared for the care of their God, etc.; i.e., they observed all that was to be observed, both with respect to God and with respect to purification, i.e., they faithfully and punctually performed their office. On משׁמרת שׁמר, see rem. on ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Genesis 26:5",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " and ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Leviticus 8:35",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". \"And (so also) the singers and doorkeepers,\" i.e., they, too, observed the duties incumbent on them. This must be mentally supplied from the beginning of the verse. \"According to the commandment of David and of Solomon his son;\" comp. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2 Chronicles 8:14",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " and ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 Chronicles 24:26",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ו must be inserted before שׁלמה, as in the lxx and Vulgate, after the analogy of ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2 Chronicles 33:7",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " and ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
